@woohgit exactly.  Definitely willing to keep an open mind on this.  The thing I want to keep for bundled plugins is good, clear documentation, so people can easily see what's there.  For the moment, PRs seem like simplest way to me to achieve it.

@PrideRage - Re: pypi-like functionality.  Since will plugins are just python packages, you can actually already do that.  Just use pypi, and specify the package in config.  This lets you use pip, setuptools, and the whole python ecosystem for package management and dependency without having to roll our own.

If people *do* start making packages that way instead of as PRs to will (let's say they're big pieces of functionality, that we all agree don't belong in core), I'd be happy to start a simple `.md` file as part of the docs that maintains a list.

