@maxcountryman Thanks for your fast reply and suggestion. I agree, that a custom decorator is probably best in this context, especially since the `current_user.username` depends on my model. Your suggestion did not work though, but never mind, it pointed me into the right direction. Now, it took me a little while before I had a chance to come up with a solution. Here is my custom decorator:

```python
def login_and_username_required(func):
    @wraps(func)
    @login_required
    def function_wrapper(*args, **kwargs):
        if kwargs is None or 'username' not in kwargs:
            raise NameError("'username' is not defined")
        elif kwargs['username'] != current_user.username:
            flash("You can only access your own directory!")
            return redirect(url_for('main.login'))
        return func(*args, **kwargs)
    return function_wrapper
```

Best and thanks again.

