@jorgemf Hi Jorge, thanks for your comment. We are aware of the estimator API as well as its mission for making distributed training transparent to users. However, a bunch of TL users would have to completely rewrite their code to fit the estimator model. Our current approach to resolve this is to provide a helper script to help them use tl.distributed to modify their program and use the train.py to bootstrap the local training. We also recommend them, in the future, to use estimator API to write their model if possible (the estimator API does not allow deep customization of the layers at this moment and we expect this would become better in the future).

We are also aware of the gRPC communication overhead. TF has some proposals to resolve using commodity hardware. However, we treat this as a separate issue with this PR. What do you think?

To sum up, the main purpose of this PR is to simply provide a helper script to start a TF_CONFIG environment locally so that existing TL programs (like the minst_distributed and inception_v3_distributed) may find easy to be setup locally. This PR does not aim to create another paradigm in parallel with the estimator.
